  "prompt": "Who are IAS Aspirants?",
  "response": "IAS aspirants are individuals who are preparing for the Indian Administrative Service (IAS) examination conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) in India. These aspirants typically aim to become civil servants, serving in various administrative capacities in the Indian government. The IAS exam is highly competitive and requires extensive preparation, including studying a wide range of subjects such as history, geography, polity, economics, current affairs, and more. Aspirants often undergo rigorous training, attend coaching classes, and engage in self-study to succeed in the examination and secure a position in the IAS.",
